Practical Information for Students
Cost of Living
The cost of living in Cyprus is relatively affordable compared to other European countries. Students can expect to spend approximately €700-€1,200 per month on living expenses, including accommodation, food, transportation, and leisure activities.

Health and Safety
Cyprus is known for its high standard of healthcare and safety. The country has modern medical facilities and a well-developed healthcare system. Students are required to have health insurance, which can be arranged through their university or Qadri International.

Transportation
Cyprus has a reliable and affordable public transportation system, including buses and taxis. Students can also consider renting bicycles or cars for convenient travel around the island.

